originalText.text: I had my first gyrotonic session a month ago and I was shocked. I have been an athlete for more than 2 decades and struggle with my flexibility. I also struggle with strengthening non major muscles that you wouldn’t typically focus on in the gym, lifting weights. During this session I was able to achieve both those goals, improving my flexibility and strength, and it was surprisingly a bit challenging which I certainly appreciate. The owner is also very kind, welcoming, and knowledgeable. I was in New York on a visit, but I would certainly return when I am back in the area.

originalText.text: Full disclosure, this is my sister's studio and growing business. With that out of the way, I had my first Gyrotonic session here 5/6/23 and it was a lovely experience, highly recommend. Even though the owner has been practicing and teaching the Gyrotonic method for years, I had never considered taking her up for a class initially. But now I work in healthcare and what I do requires standing a lot and sometimes weird positions so I finally asked her for a session. For my session we focused on my upper body and back and it felt so good! Not only did my spine and ribs feel lengthened it was also just a relaxing session that allows you to reconnect with your body. The best way I can describe it was a mix between vinyasa flow yoga and pilates, lots of intentional movement with breaths. I think it's worth trying and this is a small intimate studio in Harlem, you get personalized attention and very experienced hands. Totally worth it, even a couple days later now my body still feels good!

originalText.text: My first time doing Gyrokinesis. Had a one-on-one and it was great. My teacher name is Ife she was very patient with me and I learned a lot about my body. My body needed some TLC and man I didn’t know you can do killer abbs on a chair sitting down. The session was focus on moving the spine in many direction. Which was needed since I sit all day. The space is small but intimate, clean and I can’t wait to sign up for next class!
